					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">I believe the Baht symbol is the best option for Bitcoin denotation however would recommend a small change, &#3647;C for BitCoin instead of just &#3647;.<br /><br />This would allow for differentiation of the two easily should they ever be listed side by side and is the same setup as the Nicaraguan córdoba which uses the US $ in its currency symbolism written as C$<br /><br />For long hand (eg. those who can&#039;t type the Baht symbol for some reason) the use of BTC can be used in place of the &#3647;C as no currency in place currently makes use of BTC as the long hand for their currency (eg. USD for US Dollar, GBP for British Pound, etc...).<br /><br />Examples:<br /><br /><b>50&#3647;C/month</b><br /><b>50 BTC/month</b></div>
